OL,6,F"I've spoken to people who've said
OL,7,Fthat was the hardest day of their
OL,8,Flife. I think for us, having found
OL,9,Fthis, this was one of the best days.
OL,11,F"We come for lunch, she has a lot of
OL,12,Fvisitors, which is wonderful."
OL,14,FThe charity Alzheimer's Disease
OL,15,FInternational describes this model of
OL,16,Fcare as a "game changer".
OL,18,FThe number of people with Dementia in
OL,19,Fthe UK is expected to rise from 900
OL,20,Fthousand to 1.4 million by 2040.
